{
  "texts": [
    "It identifies ambiguities or underspecified elements and reformulates them into clearer sub-questions if needed.",
    "For complex or multi-hop queries, it produces a structured plan P = {s 1, s 2,.",
    ", s n }, where each s i denotes a reasoning subtask.",
    "The number of reasoning steps is determined by the Planner, and at each step the system performs a Retrieve → Answer RAG process using a sub-query refined by the Step Definer.",
    "Breaking down questions into simpler, targeted sub-queries enables more precise retrieval, and our empirical results across benchmarks validate this design."
  ]
}